<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-457-056  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 457 056.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  May 22 1990 v139 pC6(N) pD8(L) 9 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>G.M. to link dealers with satellite system. (Company News)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Judge, Paul C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>General Motors Corp announces it will implement the world'slargest private satellite communications network to link its manydealers with the home office.andP;  GM is contracting with HughesElectronics to provide the service, which includes a six-footsatellite dish for every dealership.andP;  GM will pay for the system,due to be installed by 1992, and the firm has told dealers the newservice will cost nothing more than the current land-basedtelephone lines.andP;  The network will allow dealers to expand theiruse of computers in diagnostic work, as well as allowing themaccess to electronic shop manuals and invoicing on GM's maincomputer.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   General Motors Corp. (communication systems).andO;Ticker:    GM.andO;Topic:     Automobile IndustrySatellite CommunicationsCommunications Satellites.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>